 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  <span style="font-weight: 400">
   This page discusses how to express the concept of 
"the ABC's" and/or how you would sign the concept of "alphabet."
   <br/>
   If instead you would like to learn the fingerspelled ABC's please visit the
   <a href="../../fingerspelling/fingerspelling.htm">
    fingerspelling page
    <font face="Arial">
     ►
    </font>
   </a>
   <font face="Arial">
   </font>
  </span>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  </p>
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
  <span style="font-weight: 400">
   <font face="Arial">
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
     To express the concept of the 
"ABC's," you spell the individual letters A, B, and C, and then you add the 
FINGERSPELL sign.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     ABC's:
     <br/>
     <object classid="CLSID:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=9,0,115,0" height="275" id="FVS1" width="320">
