      <param name="allowfullscreen" value="true"/>
      <embed allowfullscreen="true" bgcolor="#ffffff" height="275" name="FVS1" pluginspage='http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer"' src="abcs_player.swf?343912508" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="320"/>
     </object>
     <br/>
     <br/>
     <img border="0" height="234" src="/images/abcs.h1.jpg" width="222"/>
     <img border="0" height="234" src="/images/abcs.h2.jpg" width="222"/>
     <img border="0" height="234" src="/images/abcs.h3.jpg" width="222"/>
     <img border="0" height="234" src="/images/abcs.h4.jpg" width="222"/>
     <img border="0" height="234" src="/images/abcs.h5.jpg" width="222"/>
    </p>
    <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
     <br/>
     You can also express the concept of "the ABC's" by spelling A-B-C and then 
signing "through"-(indexing a horizontal list) and then "Z."
     <br/>
     <br/>
     <object classid="CLSID:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=9,0,115,0" height="275" id="FVS0" width="320">
      <param name="movie" value="abc-z_player.swf?154064346"/>
      <param name="bgcolor" value="#ffffff"/>
      <param name="allowfullscreen" value="true"/>
      <embed allowfullscreen="true" bgcolor="#ffffff" height="275" name="FVS0" pluginspage='http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer"' src="abc-z_player.swf?154064346" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="320"/>
     </object>
     <br/>
    </p>
    <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
     <br/>
     If you need to be even "more" clear, you could sign:
     <br/>
     ABC through Z  and then use your index fingers to indicate that you are 
talking about the letters as a "set."
     <br/>
    </p>
